  "prompt": "What would you do and how would you feel if you found out you had a child you'd never met?",
  "response": "Discovering that you have a child you've never met would likely evoke a wide range of emotions and thoughts. Initially, you might feel surprised or shocked by the news, especially if it was entirely unexpected. This revelation could lead to feelings of curiosity and a strong desire to learn more about the child's life and the circumstances surrounding their upbringing.\n\nEmotionally, you might experience excitement and hope at the possibility of developing a relationship with your child. At the same time, there could be anxiety or apprehension about how to approach the situation and how your presence might affect the child's life. You might also grapple with feelings of guilt or regret for not being part of the child\u2019s life up until this point.\n\nPractically, you would likely want to reach out to learn more and understand the situation better. It would be important to consider the child's feelings and needs, as well as the dynamics with their other parent or guardian. Establishing open and respectful communication would be key, as would taking steps to gradually build a connection with the child if that aligns with everyone\u2019s wishes.\n\nOverall, navigating such a complex situation would require sensitivity, patience, and a willingness to adapt while respecting the needs and boundaries of all involved.",
